.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFB2C838FF72F903FAF82404" blockId="8.[136,1452,1382,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<materialsCitation id="3B0CE36AFFB2C838FF72F903FA872405" collectionCode="LY, MPU, P, GRM" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
Michel Gandoger (1850–1926) was a French botanist and his herbarium is currently kept at 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FB1DF902FB4A25A8" box="[1234,1265,1671,1697]" country="France" name="Laboratoire de Mycologie associe au CNRS" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">LY</collectionCode>
, with duplicates present in many herbaria (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB2C838FE7CF92FFD7B25CC" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[435,704,1706,1733]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refId="ref9101" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976) Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types 1. Ed. 2. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht, 1136 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 4863" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Despite this, we have been unable to locate any further original material in his own herbarium or in the other consulted herbaria where Gandoger exsicata are distributed (e.g., 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FA4AF94AFA1F25E0" box="[1413,1444,1743,1769]" country="France" name="Laboratoire de Mycologie associe au CNRS" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">LY</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FF47F976FF732404" box="[136,200,1779,1805]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15519" name="Université Montpellier 2" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="Herbarium">MPU</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FF1CF976FF592404" box="[211,226,1779,1805]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
, etc.). Therefore, we designate the specimen at 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FD39F977FC822405" box="[758,825,1778,1804]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13654" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13654" name="Muséum d'Histoire Naturelle de Grenoble" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="Herbarium">GRM</collectionCode>
, as the 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFB2C838FC44F977FC492405" box="[907,1010,1778,1804]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FB4BF976FA872405" authorityName="Ferrer-Gallego &amp; Mateo &amp; Rosselló &amp; Sáez" authorityYear="2021" box="[1156,1340,1779,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microscapum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FB4BF976FA872405" box="[1156,1340,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. microscapum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDBE937FFB2C838FF72F893FE882495" blockId="8.[136,1452,1382,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FF72F893FE162439" bold="true" box="[189,429,1814,1840]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FE1FF892FD5E2439" authorityName="Ferrer-Gallego &amp; Mateo &amp; Rosselló &amp; Sáez" authorityYear="2021" box="[464,741,1815,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microscapum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FE1FF892FD5E2439" box="[464,741,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Hieracium microscapum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FBC5F892FB7A2439" box="[1034,1217,1815,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="majoricanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FBC5F892FB7A2439" box="[1034,1217,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. majoricanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as indicated by 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FAB7F892FA2B2438" box="[1400,1424,1815,1841]" country="Finland" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15618" name="University of Helsinki" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="Herbarium">H</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="ED7571F2FFB2C838FA5CF892FA1C2438" box="[1427,1447,1815,1841]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15678" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland, Leiden University branch" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="Herbarium">L</collectionCode>
. Sudre. All evidences indicate that it is a non mature flowering specimen of the later, which is currently growing at the 
<typeStatus id="54DF5795FFB2C838FF47F8DAFF032470" box="[136,184,1887,1913]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">type</typeStatus>
locality. The alleged identity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6492B4FFB2C838FD8DF8DAFD5E2471" box="[578,741,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elisaeanum">
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FD8DF8DAFD5E2471" box="[578,741,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">H. elisaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB2C838FD3CF8DBFCC42471" author="Mateo, G." box="[755,895,1886,1912]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="25 - 71" refId="ref8365" refString="Mateo, G. (2008) Revision sintetica del genero Hieracium L. en Espana, V. Sect. Cerinthoidea. Flora Montiberica 38: 25 - 71." type="journal article" year="2008">Mateo 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF594C6FFB2C838FC44F8DAFBC62471" author="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F." box="[907,1149,1886,1913]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" refId="ref8422" refString="Mateo, G. &amp; Egido, F. del (2017) Estudio monografico de los generos Hieracium y Pilosella en Espana. Con referencias a Portugal y los Pirineos franceses. Monografias de Botanica Iberica, nº 20, Jolube, Jaca, 422 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mateo &amp; Egido 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Mateo 
<emphasis id="B9103525FFB2C838FB17F8DAFAB22471" box="[1240,1289,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">et al</emphasis>
. 2017) should not be verified.
</paragraph>
